    <node id="&quot;ARTHUR RACKHAM&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Arthur Rackham was an English book illustrator known for his imaginative and detailed illustrations in books such as 'A Christmas Carol'."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9e3921da66da5d761ab73cd849af6c43</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;J. B. LIPPINCOTT COMPANY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"J. B. Lippincott Company was a Philadelphia and New York-based publisher responsible for publishing the 1915 edition of 'A Christmas Carol'."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9e3921da66da5d761ab73cd849af6c43</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PHILADELPHIA&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Philadelphia is a city in the United States and was home to J. B. Lippincott Company, the publisher of the 1915 edition of 'A Christmas Carol'."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9e3921da66da5d761ab73cd849af6c43</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;NEW YORK&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
      <data key="d1">"New York is a city in the United States where J. B. Lippincott Company, the publisher of the 1915 edition of 'A Christmas Carol', was also based."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9e3921da66da5d761ab73cd849af6c43</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;A CHRISTMAS CAROL&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Christmas Carol is a novel by Charles Dickens. Mentioned in the text as the subject of the Project Gutenberg eBook."&lt;SEP&gt;"A Christmas Carol is a novella by Charles Dickens, focusing on the transformation of Ebenezer Scrooge through supernatural visits from the ghosts of Christmas Past, Present, and Yet to Come."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9e3921da66da5d761ab73cd849af6c43&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-194cd9680f4967f48bea89678f7ece21</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;BOB CRATCHIT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Bob Cratchit is Scrooge's clerk, a kind and humble man who enjoys simple pleasures, such as sliding with the boys on Cornhill during Christmas Eve."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bob Cratchit is Scrooge's clerk, struggling financially but blessed by the Spirit during Christmas."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bob Cratchit is Scrooge's employee, to whom Scrooge decides to send a large turkey as a gesture meant to surprise and delight."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bob Cratchit is Scrooge's employee, who receives a surprise raise and support from Scrooge for his struggling family."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bob Cratchit is a family man, hosting a Christmas dinner and expressing gratitude for his family's gathering. He appreciates Mrs. Cratchit's culinary efforts."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bob Cratchit is a kind and mild-mannered man who wishes to drink to Scrooge's health out of respect for Christmas Day."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bob Cratchit is a loving father and husband, who is deeply affected by the loss of Tiny Tim and is grateful for the kindness of others."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bob Cratchit is an employee of Scrooge and a devoted family man, his household is experiencing the emotional impact of a recent loss, deeply affected by the situation."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bob Cratchit is an underpaid clerk working for Ebenezer Scrooge, characterized by his kindness and dedication to his family."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bob Cratchit is the father in the Cratchit family, known for his high spirits and devotion to his family."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-b0f459f5af1c3a5e0b92cbe4ee48b77b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9e3921da66da5d761ab73cd849af6c43&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1d4b58de5429cd1261370c231c8673e8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-83ac129dc9b56f84c46760d153d68e93&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-19d72c57ae3408758b18d2568e86dc6b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-503f0bfa5453467c7c61d160a3540eca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-90b95db5c53e4364a6bee36b7aa4d70f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d9aac3484185ac66045df92214d245d5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7e2e7ebcc19a53b399dc03aded4743e7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-94bea83e7153fc2064aa382b494936a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PETER CRATCHIT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Peter Cratchit is a son in the Cratchit family, noted for his enthusiastic participation in Christmas preparations."&lt;SEP&gt;"Peter Cratchit is one of the Cratchit children, characterized by a moment of stillness and quietness as he reads a book to the family."&lt;SEP&gt;"Peter Cratchit is one of the Cratchit children, who is amused by the idea of being a man of business and contemplates future investments."&lt;SEP&gt;"Peter Cratchit is the son of Bob Cratchit, part of the Cratchit family featured in 'A Christmas Carol'."&lt;SEP&gt;"Peter is the eldest Cratchit child, dutiful and observant of family matters, with prospects of a better situation suggested by Bob."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-1d4b58de5429cd1261370c231c8673e8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9e3921da66da5d761ab73cd849af6c43&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-83ac129dc9b56f84c46760d153d68e93&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-19d72c57ae3408758b18d2568e86dc6b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7e2e7ebcc19a53b399dc03aded4743e7</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;TIM CRATCHIT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Tim Cratchit, also known as 'Tiny Tim', is the youngest and disabled son of Bob Cratchit, known for his optimistic phrase 'God bless us, every one!'"</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9e3921da66da5d761ab73cd849af6c43</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MR. FEZZIWIG&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Mr. Fezziwig is a jovial and kind-hearted merchant and former employer of Ebenezer Scrooge, representing the spirit of generosity and joy."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9e3921da66da5d761ab73cd849af6c43</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;FRED&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Fred is Scrooge's nephew, characterized by his laughter and attempts to engage Scrooge, highlighting Fred's patience and willingness to give Scrooge a chance each year."&lt;SEP&gt;"Fred is Scrooge's nephew, to whom Scrooge speaks and expresses a desire to join for dinner, indicating a familial relationship."&lt;SEP&gt;"Fred is Scrooge's nephew, who participates in a game and expresses merry sentiments towards his uncle."&lt;SEP&gt;"Fred is Scrooge's nephew, who warmly welcomes Scrooge to a family dinner."&lt;SEP&gt;"Fred is Scrooge's nephew, whom Scrooge visits, signifying reconciliation and familial bonds."&lt;SEP&gt;"Fred is the cheerful and warm-hearted nephew of Ebenezer Scrooge, who consistently invites his uncle to Christmas celebrations."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9e3921da66da5d761ab73cd849af6c43&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-773d0df1dd25c356f7b771d780583e09&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8f738cb25d60a7dab782162d9d0a25ed&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-89777b838d5447c7bd1ec11282c4ee89&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-94bea83e7153fc2064aa382b494936a1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e7637ff18c5ded77a68cce0a87883fad</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;GHOST OF CHRISTMAS PAST&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Ghost of Christmas Past is a phantom that shows Ebenezer Scrooge his own past, intending to guide him toward redemption."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Ghost of Christmas Past is a spectral character who reminds Scrooge of his past, inducing moments of self-reflection and awareness."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Ghost of Christmas Past is a supernatural entity that visits Scrooge to show him scenes from his past. It is gentle but firm, aiming to aid Scrooge's reclamation."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-bb21d58d36c6306fd8810ddd51c4a971&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9e3921da66da5d761ab73cd849af6c43&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-43c9bee23adfa77aa9dedd22401bba7d</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;GHOST OF CHRISTMAS PRESENT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Ghost of Christmas Present is a jolly, giant spirit who guides Scrooge on a journey to show him the joy and spirit of the current Christmas."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Ghost of Christmas Present is a spectral being present at the celebrations, seen as knowing participants' actions during the festivities."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Ghost of Christmas Present is a spirit that embodies generosity, revealing current Christmas celebrations to Ebenezer Scrooge."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Ghost of Christmas Present is one of the supernatural entities that visited Scrooge to alter his view on life."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-90b95db5c53e4364a6bee36b7aa4d70f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-843b5b2f944c7413d9ca876e2e2f151f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9e3921da66da5d761ab73cd849af6c43&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-43c9bee23adfa77aa9dedd22401bba7d</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;GHOST OF CHRISTMAS YET TO COME&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Ghost of Christmas Yet to Come is a significant event marked by the presence of a silent specter showing Scrooge his future."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Ghost of Christmas Yet to Come is an ominous apparition that shows Ebenezer Scrooge the consequences of his actions if he does not change."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-02baee20cc9463dbe08170a8e1043e32&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9e3921da66da5d761ab73cd849af6c43</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;GHOST OF JACOB MARLEY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Jacob Marley is the ghost of Scrooge's former business partner, appearing to warn Ebenezer Scrooge and urge him to change his ways."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9e3921da66da5d761ab73cd849af6c43</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;JOE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Joe is a marine-store dealer known for dealing in stolen goods, included in 'A Christmas Carol'."&lt;SEP&gt;"Joe is someone engaged in a conversation about taking bed-curtains, indicating involvement in a transaction or exchange."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9e3921da66da5d761ab73cd849af6c43&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-89777b838d5447c7bd1ec11282c4ee89</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;EBENEZER SCROOGE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Ebenezer Scrooge is a central character portrayed as a man of business, who experiences a supernatural visitation by a ghost."&lt;SEP&gt;"Ebenezer Scrooge is a character experiencing confusion and anxiety about time and his experiences, particularly haunted by Marley's Ghost."&lt;SEP&gt;"Ebenezer Scrooge is a miserly old man and the protagonist of 'A Christmas Carol', who undergoes a profound transformation."&lt;SEP&gt;"Ebenezer Scrooge is a wealthy man known for his miserly attitude and disdain for Christmas, often isolating himself from others."&lt;SEP&gt;"Ebenezer Scrooge is portrayed as a young man, former apprentice of Fezziwig, who reflects on his past with nostalgia."&lt;SEP&gt;"Ebenezer Scrooge is the main character experiencing interactions with supernatural entities. He is initially skeptical and dismissive but becomes increasingly reflective and emotional as he revisits his past."&lt;SEP&gt;"Scrooge is a skeptical and cold-hearted man who is confronted by Marley's Ghost in this scene."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8bc1edd983869352d14cf0886a9175a7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9e3921da66da5d761ab73cd849af6c43&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-359187e7571bda4b0b08b2e0b6581e52&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-773d0df1dd25c356f7b771d780583e09&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bb21d58d36c6306fd8810ddd51c4a971&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1aa50206d02ed89418f65f97c6441d1c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c7b10789a9cb0af6c553730b29bd9034</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MR. TOPPER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Mr. Topper is a bachelor who attends Fred's Christmas party, known for his humorous and flirtatious behavior."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9e3921da66da5d761ab73cd849af6c43</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;DICK WILKINS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Dick Wilkins is Scrooge's fellow apprentice and former colleague, who was very attached to Scrooge."&lt;SEP&gt;"Dick Wilkins is a fellow apprentice of Scrooge, remembered affectionately by Scrooge as someone who was attached to him."&lt;SEP&gt;"Dick Wilkins was a fellow apprentice of Ebenezer Scrooge during their youth, remembered fondly by Scrooge."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8bc1edd983869352d14cf0886a9175a7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9e3921da66da5d761ab73cd849af6c43&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c6c248858d1b13ab7ee9ca13c1aeed6b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;BELLE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Belle is Scrooge's former love, now married and happy with her family, representing a life that Scrooge could have had."&lt;SEP&gt;"Belle is an old sweetheart of Ebenezer Scrooge who ended their relationship due to his growing obsession with wealth."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9e3921da66da5d761ab73cd849af6c43&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-da2472b4ef2a535b62908f14d0fb0ca9</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CAROLINE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Caroline is a character whose family is financially indebted, experiencing a mix of hope and guilt upon learning of a creditor's death, seeing it as a potential reprieve from financial burden."&lt;SEP&gt;"Caroline is the wife of one of Scrooge's debtors, relieved upon learning of his potential death."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9e3921da66da5d761ab73cd849af6c43&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-83ac129dc9b56f84c46760d153d68e93</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MRS. CRATCHIT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Mrs. Cratchit is Bob Cratchit's wife, dressed modestly but cheerfully for Christmas celebrations."&lt;SEP&gt;"Mrs. Cratchit is Bob Cratchit's wife, notable for her successful preparation of the Christmas pudding, which is greatly admired by the family."&lt;SEP&gt;"Mrs. Cratchit is Bob's wife, who strongly voices her discontent with Scrooge but agrees to drink to his health for the sake of Christmas Day."&lt;SEP&gt;"Mrs. Cratchit is a family member who shows affection to Bob and shares the familial bond with the Cratchit family."&lt;SEP&gt;"Mrs. Cratchit is the mother in the Cratchit family, involved in managing Christmas preparations and caring for her family."&lt;SEP&gt;"Mrs. Cratchit is the wife of Bob Cratchit, known for her strength and dedication to her family."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-b0f459f5af1c3a5e0b92cbe4ee48b77b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9e3921da66da5d761ab73cd849af6c43&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-91572b3cd42786ba4cb2f180ca25cbf4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-19d72c57ae3408758b18d2568e86dc6b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-503f0bfa5453467c7c61d160a3540eca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7e2e7ebcc19a53b399dc03aded4743e7</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;BELINDA CRATCHIT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Belinda Cratchit is the daughter of Bob Cratchit, part of the Cratchit family."&lt;SEP&gt;"Belinda Cratchit is the second daughter of Bob and Mrs. Cratchit, assisting in preparing the Christmas meal."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-b0f459f5af1c3a5e0b92cbe4ee48b77b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9e3921da66da5d761ab73cd849af6c43</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MARTHA CRATCHIT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Martha Cratchit is a daughter in the Cratchit family, involved in the family's Christmas preparations."&lt;SEP&gt;"Martha Cratchit is a poor apprentice at a milliner's who works long hours and enjoys spending her holiday at home with family."&lt;SEP&gt;"Martha Cratchit is the daughter of Bob Cratchit and the eldest of the Cratchit children."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-19d72c57ae3408758b18d2568e86dc6b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9e3921da66da5d761ab73cd849af6c43&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7e2e7ebcc19a53b399dc03aded4743e7</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MRS. DILBER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Mrs. Dilber is a character who participates in selling items to Old Joe, connected to the themes of self-interest and survival."&lt;SEP&gt;"Mrs. Dilber is a laundress who appears in 'A Christmas Carol', known for selling Scrooge's belongings after his death."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9e3921da66da5d761ab73cd849af6c43&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-60fc063c79fc0d4acc91a57e79de04dc</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;FAN&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Fan is Scrooge's younger sister, portrayed as a joyful and caring individual who brings Scrooge home with excitement."&lt;SEP&gt;"Fan is the deceased sister of Ebenezer Scrooge, remembered nostalgically by Scrooge during his visits to the past."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9e3921da66da5d761ab73cd849af6c43&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c6c248858d1b13ab7ee9ca13c1aeed6b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MRS. FEZZIWIG&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Mrs. Fezziwig is Fezziwig's partner, involved in hosting the festive dance alongside him."&lt;SEP&gt;"Mrs. Fezziwig is mentioned as someone dancing with Fezziwig, implying her involvement in social or festive activities."&lt;SEP&gt;"Mrs. Fezziwig is the wife of Fezziwig, described as substantial and full of warmth and matching Fezziwig with her dancing skills."&lt;SEP&gt;"Mrs. Fezziwig is the wife of Mr. Fezziwig, known for her lively spirit and participation in their joyful Christmas celebrations."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8bc1edd983869352d14cf0886a9175a7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9e3921da66da5d761ab73cd849af6c43&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-89777b838d5447c7bd1ec11282c4ee89&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b2f98bc7abb0c67d4c86055c7fd72218</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MARLEY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Marley is Scrooge's deceased business partner who appears as a ghostly image in the door knocker, creating a supernatural element in the story."&lt;SEP&gt;"Marley is a deceased individual, associated with a ghostly presence that Scrooge encounters. His face is a recurring image in Scrooge's mind, and he is tied to a spectral event."&lt;SEP&gt;"Marley is mentioned as someone from Scrooge's past with whom he shared the experience of cold winters, hinting at a connection in Scrooge's history."&lt;SEP&gt;"Marley was Scrooge's business partner, now deceased. He is recognized as the former co-owner of Scrooge and Marley, with his name still prominently displayed on the warehouse."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-843b5b2f944c7413d9ca876e2e2f151f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-89777b838d5447c7bd1ec11282c4ee89&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d9aac3484185ac66045df92214d245d5</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;FEZZIWIG&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Fezziwig is Scrooge’s former employer, remembered fondly by Scrooge for his jovial and benevolent nature."&lt;SEP&gt;"Fezziwig is a cheerful and generous character who hosts a festive dance and is praised by his apprentices for his ability to make others happy."&lt;SEP&gt;"Fezziwig is a jovial and kind-hearted employer, who organizes a Christmas Eve party for his employees and shows agility despite his age."&lt;SEP&gt;"Fezziwig is an individual mentioned in association with a dance, suggesting participation in festive or communal events."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8bc1edd983869352d14cf0886a9175a7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-89777b838d5447c7bd1ec11282c4ee89&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b2f98bc7abb0c67d4c86055c7fd72218&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c6c248858d1b13ab7ee9ca13c1aeed6b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;OLD SCRATCH&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Old Scratch is a colloquial reference implying the devil or death, noted in conversation as having claimed someone, likely a wealthy individual."&lt;SEP&gt;"Old Scratch is a colloquial reference to the devil, used here in conversation to imply that someone has gotten what they deserve."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-f1a4fbcf1ed86864b9bfd5e8dba4c683&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-89777b838d5447c7bd1ec11282c4ee89</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;TIM&quot;">
