    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CAMDEN TOWN&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Camden Town is a location mentioned as the place where Bob Cratchit runs home to after leaving work on Christmas Eve."&lt;SEP&gt;"Camden Town is the location mentioned as the destination for the turkey delivery."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8f738cb25d60a7dab782162d9d0a25ed&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d9aac3484185ac66045df92214d245d5</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CITY OF LONDON&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The City of London is where Scrooge lives and works, representing the bustling, commercial backdrop to his life."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d9aac3484185ac66045df92214d245d5</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE COUNTING-HOUSE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Counting-house is Scrooge's place of business, where he works and interacts with Bob Cratchit."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d9aac3484185ac66045df92214d245d5</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE FOG AND FROST&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Fog and Frost are atmospheric conditions that contribute to the gloomy and cold setting of the story."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d9aac3484185ac66045df92214d245d5</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE KNOCKER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Knocker event refers to the moment when Scrooge sees Marley's face in the door knocker, a supernatural occurrence that unsettles him."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Knocker is a door knocker that Scrooge expresses affection for, seeing it as a symbol of his newfound appreciation for life."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8f738cb25d60a7dab782162d9d0a25ed&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d9aac3484185ac66045df92214d245d5</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MARLEY'S GHOST&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Marley's Ghost is an unearthly visitor haunting Scrooge, causing him to question whether his experiences are dreams or reality."&lt;SEP&gt;"Marley's Ghost refers to the supernatural appearance of Jacob Marley's spirit, delivering a crucial warning to Scrooge on Christmas Eve."&lt;SEP&gt;"Marley's Ghost represents a supernatural occurrence involving the specter of Scrooge's former associate, Marley, which has a profound impact on Scrooge."&lt;SEP&gt;"Marley's Ghost represents the apparition of Jacob Marley appearing before Scrooge to deliver a message, serving as a pivotal event that initiates Scrooge's transformation."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-c7b10789a9cb0af6c553730b29bd9034&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1aa50206d02ed89418f65f97c6441d1c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cb661c37436355ccec2769b1d0350c5f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;DUTCH MERCHANT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Dutch Merchant is referenced as the builder of Scrooge's fireplace, adding historical context to Scrooge's setting."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE WINE-MERCHANT'S CELLAR&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Wine-Merchant's Cellar is an underground location in Scrooge's house, associated with echoing sounds and ghostly chains."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE BELL&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Bell is a disused object in Scrooge's room that rings mysteriously, signaling the arrival of Marley's Ghost."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE LOCOMOTIVE HEARSE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Locomotive Hearse is a spectral image that Scrooge imagines going up the stairs, adding to the eerie atmosphere of the text."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CAINS AND ABELS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Cains and Abels refer to the biblical imagery depicted on the tiles of Scrooge's fireplace, which captures his attention."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PHARAOH'S DAUGHTER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Pharaoh's Daughter is among the biblical figures illustrated on the Dutch tiles in Scrooge's fireplace."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;QUEENS OF SHEBA&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Queens of Sheba are biblical figures depicted on the tiles of Scrooge's fireplace, contributing to the religious ambiance."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ANGELIC MESSENGERS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Angelic Messengers are another set of biblical references depicted on Scrooge's fireplace tiles."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;APOSTLES IN BUTTER-BOATS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Apostles in Butter-boats refer to an unusual biblical depiction found on the tiles of Scrooge's fireplace."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;JACOB MARLEY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Jacob Marley is Scrooge's deceased business partner, who plays a role in sending spirits to guide Scrooge."&lt;SEP&gt;"Jacob Marley is Scrooge's former business partner, now appearing as a ghost burdened by chains made of various business-related items."&lt;SEP&gt;"Jacob Marley is a deceased character who influences Scrooge's transformation and reflection on Christmas."&lt;SEP&gt;"Jacob Marley is a deceased former business partner of Scrooge, whose prediction about Spirits visiting Scrooge sets the context for the narrative."&lt;SEP&gt;"Jacob Marley is mentioned by Scrooge, likely as a reference to a past interaction that has significantly impacted Scrooge's perspective."&lt;SEP&gt;"Jacob Marley is referenced as someone from Scrooge's past, whose death had an impact on Scrooge, prompting introspection prompted by Scrooge's reflection on past kindnesses."&lt;SEP&gt;"Jacob Marley is the deceased partner of Scrooge, who appears as a ghost, warning Scrooge about the consequences of his worldly life."&lt;SEP&gt;"Jacob Marley is the ghost of Scrooge's former business partner who appears to warn Scrooge about the consequences of living a life focused solely on wealth."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-43c9bee23adfa77aa9dedd22401bba7d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-91572b3cd42786ba4cb2f180ca25cbf4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-da2472b4ef2a535b62908f14d0fb0ca9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-359187e7571bda4b0b08b2e0b6581e52&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-90b95db5c53e4364a6bee36b7aa4d70f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cb661c37436355ccec2769b1d0350c5f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1aa50206d02ed89418f65f97c6441d1c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-02baee20cc9463dbe08170a8e1043e32</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE CHAIN&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Chain represents Marley's Ghost's burden, made of cash-boxes, keys, padlocks, ledgers, deeds, and heavy purses, symbolizing the weight of his past greed."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-1aa50206d02ed89418f65f97c6441d1c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SPECTRE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Spectre is another term used to describe Marley's Ghost, highlighting its ghastly and supernatural presence."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-1aa50206d02ed89418f65f97c6441d1c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;INFERNAL ATMOSPHERE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Infernal Atmosphere refers to the unnatural and unsettling aura surrounding Marley's Ghost, as if it is surrounded by hot vapour."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-1aa50206d02ed89418f65f97c6441d1c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE TOOTHPICK&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Toothpick is used by Scrooge as a tool to distract himself and challenge the reality of the ghostly apparition."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-1aa50206d02ed89418f65f97c6441d1c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE BANDAGE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Bandage is wrapped around Marley's Ghost's head and chin, which he removes to reveal his jaw dropping, symbolizing his spectral condition."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-1aa50206d02ed89418f65f97c6441d1c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE GHOST&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Ghost is a spirit that accompanies Scrooge, showing him various scenes and teaching moral lessons."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Ghost is a spiritual entity that guides Scrooge through his memories, prompting reflections on his past and insights into his character."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Ghost is a supernatural entity guiding Scrooge through different locations and experiences linked to Christmas."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Ghost is a supernatural entity guiding Scrooge through reflections of his past, emphasizing the impact of seemingly small acts of kindness."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Ghost is a supernatural entity that reveals potential future events concerning Tiny Tim's health, prompting reflection from Scrooge."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Ghost is a supernatural presence guiding Scrooge through memories of his past, eliciting reflections and emotions."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Ghost is referenced in the story, appearing alongside Scrooge during the Christmas activities, observing and interacting with him."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Ghost is the spectral appearance of Jacob Marley, who warns Scrooge about his fate and the impending visit from the Three Spirits."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Ghost is the spirit of Jacob Marley, appearing to Scrooge to convey a message about the mistakes of his life and the importance of focusing on humanity."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-43c9bee23adfa77aa9dedd22401bba7d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-359187e7571bda4b0b08b2e0b6581e52&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-503f0bfa5453467c7c61d160a3540eca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cb661c37436355ccec2769b1d0350c5f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-91614df5cb74cbe5e109a338a82041e9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b2f98bc7abb0c67d4c86055c7fd72218&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c6c248858d1b13ab7ee9ca13c1aeed6b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e7637ff18c5ded77a68cce0a87883fad&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8590d9263cd2cd4fa583c432fc54e6c3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;WARD&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Ward is mentioned as a place, possibly a jurisdiction where public disturbances like the ghost's cries can be taken as legal nuisances."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-359187e7571bda4b0b08b2e0b6581e52</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;WORLDLY MIND&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The concept of having a practical, material focus, as addressed by the Ghost when confronting Scrooge."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-359187e7571bda4b0b08b2e0b6581e52</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CHAINS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Chains represent the emotional and spiritual burdens borne by Marley in the afterlife as a consequence of his earthly actions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-359187e7571bda4b0b08b2e0b6581e52</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CHRISTMAS EVES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The time reference used by the Ghost to signify the duration of Marley's torment and Scrooge's accumulating burden."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-359187e7571bda4b0b08b2e0b6581e52</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MINISTER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ROLE"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Minister refers to the conveyers of messages from other regions, as mentioned by the Ghost of Marley."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-359187e7571bda4b0b08b2e0b6581e52</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE THREE SPIRITS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Three Spirits are supernatural entities that Marley's Ghost warns will visit Scrooge to guide him towards redemption."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cb661c37436355ccec2769b1d0350c5f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE PHANTOMS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Phantoms are restless spirits witnessed by Scrooge, wearing chains and lamenting their past, representing the consequences of their earthly lives."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cb661c37436355ccec2769b1d0350c5f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SCROOGE'S CHAMBER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Scrooge's Chamber is the setting where Scrooge encounters Marley's Ghost and contemplates the supernatural occurrences."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cb661c37436355ccec2769b1d0350c5f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THREE SPIRITS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Three Spirits are the supernatural visitors predicted by Marley's Ghost to guide Scrooge towards self-reflection and redemption."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cb661c37436355ccec2769b1d0350c5f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE PHANTOM WITH IRON SAFE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Phantom with Iron Safe is a ghost that is familiar to Scrooge, symbolizing the burdens and regrets of wealth-hoarding in life."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cb661c37436355ccec2769b1d0350c5f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE INFANTS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Infants are the figures seen by the Ghosts, representing innocence and need, highlighting the regret the Phantoms feel for being unable to assist."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cb661c37436355ccec2769b1d0350c5f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;FIRST OF EXCHANGE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The First of Exchange is a financial event mentioned in Scrooge's thoughts regarding a security transaction, highlighting his preoccupation with financial matters."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-c7b10789a9cb0af6c553730b29bd9034</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE GHOST OF CHRISTMAS PAST&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Ghost of Christmas Past is a supernatural visitor that appears to Scrooge, possessing a childlike yet aged appearance with features that fluctuate in clarity and form."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-c7b10789a9cb0af6c553730b29bd9034</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SCROOGE'S ROOM&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Scrooge's Room is the setting where much of the supernatural visitation occurs, highlighted by its dark and foggy atmosphere."&lt;SEP&gt;"Scrooge's Room undergoes a magical transformation by the Spirit, filled with festive decorations and a feast, symbolizing abundance and joy."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-c7b10789a9cb0af6c553730b29bd9034&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-843b5b2f944c7413d9ca876e2e2f151f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE CLOCK&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Clock represents Scrooge’s obsession and confusion about time, as he tries to make sense of its seemingly erratic chiming."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-c7b10789a9cb0af6c553730b29bd9034</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MARKET-TOWN&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The market-town is a geographic location from Scrooge's past, described with a bridge, church, and winding river. It represents memories of Scrooge's childhood."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-bb21d58d36c6306fd8810ddd51c4a971</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SCROOGE'S CHILDHOOD HOME AND SCHOOL&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Scrooge's childhood home and school are geographic locations significant in his past, associated with his emotional reflections and solitude."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-bb21d58d36c6306fd8810ddd51c4a971</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SPIRIT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Spirit is a supernatural being accompanying Scrooge, spreading goodwill and joy with his torch's power."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Spirit is a supernatural entity guiding Scrooge and teaching him lessons about his life and future."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Spirit is another term used for the Ghost of Christmas Past, embodying supernatural guidance that aims to help Scrooge through his past memories."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Spirit is another term used for the Ghost that compels Scrooge to witness scenes from his past."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Spirit refers to the supernatural being, the Ghost of Christmas Present, who is guiding Scrooge on a transformative journey."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-b0f459f5af1c3a5e0b92cbe4ee48b77b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-54bdd22db1f84a965b5f4c06c9216d8d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-843b5b2f944c7413d9ca876e2e2f151f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bb21d58d36c6306fd8810ddd51c4a971&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-02baee20cc9463dbe08170a8e1043e32</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;FIELDS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The fields are part of the rural landscape from Scrooge’s past that are filled with merry music and joyful travelers, contributing to Scrooge's nostalgia."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-bb21d58d36c6306fd8810ddd51c4a971</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;BOYS ON PONIES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The event of boys riding ponies is part of Scrooge's cheerful memories, displaying youthful joy and camaraderie during Christmas."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-bb21d58d36c6306fd8810ddd51c4a971</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CROSS-ROADS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Cross-roads represents a geographic location where people part ways, evoking a sense of camaraderie and festive spirit remembered by Scrooge."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-bb21d58d36c6306fd8810ddd51c4a971</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SNOW&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Snow covers the ground during the wintry walk with the Spirit, signifying the cold, clear winter day that contrasts with the warmth of Scrooge's memories."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-bb21d58d36c6306fd8810ddd51c4a971</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SCROOGE'S BOYHOOD FRIENDS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The people from Scrooge's past, who he recognizes and feels joy seeing again, emphasize his emotional connection to a time long gone."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-bb21d58d36c6306fd8810ddd51c4a971</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ALI BABA&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Ali Baba is a fictional character mentioned by Scrooge, representing part of the imaginary stories that comforted him as a lonely child."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8590d9263cd2cd4fa583c432fc54e6c3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;VALENTINE AND ORSON&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Valentine and Orson are characters from folk tales that Scrooge recalls, illustrating his vivid imagination and childhood escape into stories."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8590d9263cd2cd4fa583c432fc54e6c3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;DAMASCUS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Damascus is a city mentioned in Scrooge's recollection of stories, symbolizing the exotic and distant realms of his childhood fantasies."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8590d9263cd2cd4fa583c432fc54e6c3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE SULTAN'S GROOM&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
