    <node id="&quot;TINY TIM&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Tiny Tim is Bob Cratchit's son, mentioned by Scrooge when comparing the turkey's size, indicative of Scrooge's newfound generosity."&lt;SEP&gt;"Tiny Tim is Bob Cratchit's son, who, due to Scrooge's newfound generosity, survives and is cherished as if by a second father."&lt;SEP&gt;"Tiny Tim is Bob Cratchit's son, whose health and spirit are central to his family's concern and whose memory evokes emotion in the narrative."&lt;SEP&gt;"Tiny Tim is Bob's son, a frail child whose health is a concern for the family. His positive spirit is evident as he echoes the Christmas blessings."&lt;SEP&gt;"Tiny Tim is a beloved child in the Cratchit family, remembered for his patience, mildness, and lightness."&lt;SEP&gt;"Tiny Tim is mentioned in reference to the size of the turkey, indicating he is a child associated with Bob."&lt;SEP&gt;"Tiny Tim is referred to as a source of patience and mildness, whose spirit has a lasting impact on the Cratchit family."&lt;SEP&gt;"Tiny Tim is the youngest child in the Cratchit family, who is physically disabled but possesses a warm spirit."&lt;SEP&gt;"Tiny Tim is the youngest of the Cratchit children, who sings a song with a plaintive voice and seems indifferent to the toast to Scrooge."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-1d4b58de5429cd1261370c231c8673e8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-91572b3cd42786ba4cb2f180ca25cbf4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-83ac129dc9b56f84c46760d153d68e93&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-19d72c57ae3408758b18d2568e86dc6b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-503f0bfa5453467c7c61d160a3540eca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-90b95db5c53e4364a6bee36b7aa4d70f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8f738cb25d60a7dab782162d9d0a25ed&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7e2e7ebcc19a53b399dc03aded4743e7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-94bea83e7153fc2064aa382b494936a1</data>
    </node>
