      <data key="d2">chunk-43c9bee23adfa77aa9dedd22401bba7d</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;TWELFTH-NIGHT PARTY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Twelfth-Night party is an event Scrooge and the Ghost visit, marking a point during their journey."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e7637ff18c5ded77a68cce0a87883fad</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;IGNORANCE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Ignorance is personified as a boy, symbolizing lack of knowledge or awareness and the potential for negative outcomes."&lt;SEP&gt;"Ignorance is personified as a wretched, abject boy brought forth by the Ghost, symbolizing the neglect of knowledge in humanity."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-02baee20cc9463dbe08170a8e1043e32&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e7637ff18c5ded77a68cce0a87883fad</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;WANT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Want is personified as a girl, symbolizing poverty and desire, highlighting societal issues."&lt;SEP&gt;"Want is personified as a wretched, abject girl brought forth by the Ghost, symbolizing the unmet needs and desires within humanity."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-02baee20cc9463dbe08170a8e1043e32&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e7637ff18c5ded77a68cce0a87883fad</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CHRISTMAS HOLIDAYS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Christmas holidays are condensed into Scrooge's experiences with the Ghost, emphasizing themes of reflection and transformation."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e7637ff18c5ded77a68cce0a87883fad</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE LAST OF THE SPIRITS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Last of the Spirits is an encounter featuring the silent and foreboding Ghost, marking the final supernatural visitation for Scrooge."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-02baee20cc9463dbe08170a8e1043e32</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MERCHANTS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Merchants are a group of business people in the City who discuss the death of a man, reflecting societal values and attitudes."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-02baee20cc9463dbe08170a8e1043e32</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;GHOST OF THE FUTURE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Ghost of the Future, also known as the Ghost of Christmas Yet to Come, is a silent specter who shows Scrooge what might happen in the future."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-02baee20cc9463dbe08170a8e1043e32</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CHANGE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Change refers to the semblance of transition or transformation, such as the possibility of Scrooge's transformation through his revelations with the Spirits."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-02baee20cc9463dbe08170a8e1043e32</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE PHANTOM&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Phantom is a ghostly figure guiding Scrooge through visions, pointing towards the future consequences of Scrooge's actions on his life."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Phantom is a mysterious and silent entity, synonymous with the Ghost of Christmas Yet to Come, who leads Scrooge through his potential future."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Phantom is an entity accompanying Scrooge, likely a supernatural presence."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Phantom is an entity guiding Scrooge through a future vision, prompting him to reflect on his life and decisions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-02baee20cc9463dbe08170a8e1043e32&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f1a4fbcf1ed86864b9bfd5e8dba4c683&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-60fc063c79fc0d4acc91a57e79de04dc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e1f29eeadc1d8ab46dc8a0bbd3c56b64</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;DOOM&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Doom is a concept represented on the brow of the boy Ignorance, symbolizing inevitable consequences unless something changes."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-02baee20cc9463dbe08170a8e1043e32</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;WORKHOUSES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Workhouses refer to institutions meant to provide work and shelter for the poor, reflecting the social attitudes of the time."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-02baee20cc9463dbe08170a8e1043e32</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PRISONS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Prisons symbolize punishment and confinement, often mentioned as a societal solution to crime and poverty."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-02baee20cc9463dbe08170a8e1043e32</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;JACOB&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Jacob is Scrooge's old partner, mentioned in connection with past events. His death is a point of reflection for Scrooge."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-f1a4fbcf1ed86864b9bfd5e8dba4c683</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE BUSINESSMEN&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Businessmen are wealthy men of importance known to Scrooge, whose conversations hint at the fate of a deceased colleague, likely impacting Scrooge."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-f1a4fbcf1ed86864b9bfd5e8dba4c683</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE NEIGHBOURHOOD&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Neighbourhood is an ill-reputed area with foul conditions, which Scrooge visits during his journey with the Phantom."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-f1a4fbcf1ed86864b9bfd5e8dba4c683</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE SHOP&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Shop is a dismal establishment in a crime-ridden area, selling scrap and run by a grey-haired rascal."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Shop owned by Old Joe is a place where second-hand goods are traded, filled with various clutter and wares for sale."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-f1a4fbcf1ed86864b9bfd5e8dba4c683&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-60fc063c79fc0d4acc91a57e79de04dc</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE FIRST SPEAKER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The First Speaker is a character who discusses the future of a deceased man's wealth and expresses a willingness to attend his funeral if others do."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-f1a4fbcf1ed86864b9bfd5e8dba4c683</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE GENTLEMAN WITH THE EXCRESCENCE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Gentleman with the Excrescence is a character whose nose is described vividly, and who humorously considers attending a funeral if food is provided."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-f1a4fbcf1ed86864b9bfd5e8dba4c683</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE MAN WITH THE LARGE CHIN&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Man with the Large Chin is a character speculating on the finding of a deceased man's wealth, suggesting it might be left to his company."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-f1a4fbcf1ed86864b9bfd5e8dba4c683</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE OTHER BUSINESSMAN&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Other Businessman participates in a brief conversation about Old Scratch claiming 'his own,' and discusses the seasonable Christmas weather."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-f1a4fbcf1ed86864b9bfd5e8dba4c683</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE CHARCOAL STOVE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Charcoal Stove is part of the shop's interior environment, used for warmth by an elderly shopkeeper."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-f1a4fbcf1ed86864b9bfd5e8dba4c683</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE ELDERLY SHOPKEEPER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Elderly Shopkeeper is a grey-haired rascal running a shop selling various old items and shielding himself from the cold with a curtain of tatters."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-f1a4fbcf1ed86864b9bfd5e8dba4c683</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;OLD JOE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Old Joe is a character involved in the sale and distribution of goods stolen from a deceased person's home."&lt;SEP&gt;"Old Joe is a grey-haired rascal running a shop, known for dealing in second-hand goods."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-60fc063c79fc0d4acc91a57e79de04dc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e1f29eeadc1d8ab46dc8a0bbd3c56b64</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE WOMAN&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Woman is a character who is actively participating in taking and selling items from a deceased person's possession."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Woman is a character who is bold and pragmatic, doing what she needs to take care of herself."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-60fc063c79fc0d4acc91a57e79de04dc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e1f29eeadc1d8ab46dc8a0bbd3c56b64</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE UNDERTAKER'S MAN&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Undertaker's Man is one of the characters selling items to Old Joe, part of a trio known for their self-serving interests."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-60fc063c79fc0d4acc91a57e79de04dc</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE LAUNDRESS&quot;">
