    <node id="&quot;SCROOGE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">Ebenezer Scrooge is a central character in the narrative, known for his miserly demeanor and stark indifference towards the plight of the poor. Initially, he maintains a strong belief in self-reliance and displays disdain for charity and Christmas festivities, embodying a cynical and grumpy attitude towards those who celebrate. Scrooge is depicted as a solitary, cold, and tight-fisted old man, whose reputation casts a dark shadow over the Cratchit family gatherings.

Throughout the story, Scrooge undergoes significant emotional turmoil and reflection as he confronts his past, realizing the consequences of his choices. Guided by the spirits, he experiences a transformative journey during which he witnesses visions that provoke feelings of nostalgia, regret, guilt, and the potential for redemption. This process involves interactions with various spirits, including the Ghost of Christmas Past, who helps him reflect on lost joys and the contrast between his former self and his current solitary existence.

Scrooge shows a newfound interest in the fate of Tiny Tim and is compelled to reconsider his indifference as he observes the joys and struggles of others during Christmas Day. By the end of his supernatural encounters, his character transforms profoundly; he moves from a miserly figure to one characterized by kindness and generosity, exemplified by his interactions with others and his decision to send a turkey as a gesture of goodwill. Ultimately, Scrooge emerges as a changed man, embracing the spirit of Christmas and committing to making amends for his past behaviors.</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-da2472b4ef2a535b62908f14d0fb0ca9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-91614df5cb74cbe5e109a338a82041e9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f1a4fbcf1ed86864b9bfd5e8dba4c683&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e7637ff18c5ded77a68cce0a87883fad&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8590d9263cd2cd4fa583c432fc54e6c3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b0f459f5af1c3a5e0b92cbe4ee48b77b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-54bdd22db1f84a965b5f4c06c9216d8d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-90d5764e301321c087f5a8f78b73a145&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-90b95db5c53e4364a6bee36b7aa4d70f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cb661c37436355ccec2769b1d0350c5f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-843b5b2f944c7413d9ca876e2e2f151f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-89777b838d5447c7bd1ec11282c4ee89&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c6c248858d1b13ab7ee9ca13c1aeed6b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-02baee20cc9463dbe08170a8e1043e32&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5dac41b3f9eeaf794f0147400b1718cd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-91572b3cd42786ba4cb2f180ca25cbf4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-503f0bfa5453467c7c61d160a3540eca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d9aac3484185ac66045df92214d245d5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b2f98bc7abb0c67d4c86055c7fd72218&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e1f29eeadc1d8ab46dc8a0bbd3c56b64&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-94bea83e7153fc2064aa382b494936a1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-43c9bee23adfa77aa9dedd22401bba7d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-60fc063c79fc0d4acc91a57e79de04dc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-83ac129dc9b56f84c46760d153d68e93&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-19d72c57ae3408758b18d2568e86dc6b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8f738cb25d60a7dab782162d9d0a25ed&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-74e2466de2f67fd710ef2f20c0a8d9e0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-99b0ec7f7e006561352b5d65e849611d</data>
