      <data key="d4">"The job opportunity could provide Peter with a steady income, manifesting Bob's plans for his son's future."</data>
      <data key="d5">chunk-19d72c57ae3408758b18d2568e86dc6b</data>
      <data key="d6">1</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;FRED&quot;" target="&quot;SCROOGE'S NEPHEW&quot;">
      <data key="d3">10.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"Fred and Scrooge's nephew are the same person, as Fred is the name of Scrooge's nephew."</data>
      <data key="d5">chunk-773d0df1dd25c356f7b771d780583e09</data>
      <data key="d6">1</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;FRED&quot;" target="&quot;SCROOGE'S NIECE&quot;">
      <data key="d3">9.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"Fred and his wife, Scrooge's niece, are both central in the social circle and holiday celebration, sharing similar views and laughter."</data>
      <data key="d5">chunk-773d0df1dd25c356f7b771d780583e09</data>
      <data key="d6">1</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;FRED&quot;" target="&quot;TOPPER&quot;">
      <data key="d3">6.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"Fred and Topper are part of the same social gathering, and Topper interacts with Fred by humorously contributing to the conversation about bachelors."</data>
      <data key="d5">chunk-773d0df1dd25c356f7b771d780583e09</data>
      <data key="d6">1</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;FRED&quot;" target="&quot;SCROOGE&quot;">
      <data key="d3">23.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"Fred, Scrooge's nephew, plays a game involving Scrooge which leads to merriment and goodwill sentiments towards him."&lt;SEP&gt;"Scrooge is Fred's uncle and is warmly invited to Fred’s Christmas dinner, marking a change in Scrooge's relational dynamics."&lt;SEP&gt;"Scrooge visits his nephew Fred, demonstrating a desire to reconnect with family and celebrate Christmas together."</data>
      <data key="d5">chunk-8f738cb25d60a7dab782162d9d0a25ed&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e7637ff18c5ded77a68cce0a87883fad&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-94bea83e7153fc2064aa382b494936a1</data>
      <data key="d6">1</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;GHOST OF CHRISTMAS PAST&quot;" target="&quot;EBENEZER SCROOGE&quot;">
      <data key="d3">8.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The Ghost of Christmas Past visits Scrooge to show him scenes from his past, enhancing his reflections on former experiences."</data>
      <data key="d5">chunk-bb21d58d36c6306fd8810ddd51c4a971</data>
      <data key="d6">1</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;GHOST OF CHRISTMAS PAST&quot;" target="&quot;SCROOGE&quot;">
      <data key="d3">8.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The presence of the Ghost of Christmas Past causes Scrooge to reflect on his past actions and moments, leading to nostalgia and self-assessment."</data>
      <data key="d5">chunk-43c9bee23adfa77aa9dedd22401bba7d</data>
      <data key="d6">1</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;GHOST OF CHRISTMAS PRESENT&quot;" target="&quot;SCROOGE&quot;">
      <data key="d3">26.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"Scrooge is guided by the Ghost of Christmas Present to learn about the joy and spirit of Christmas, contrasting with his past behavior."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Ghost of Christmas Present is one of the spirits that has visited Scrooge, helping shift his mindset towards kindness and generosity."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Ghost of Christmas Present observes and guides Scrooge, providing opportunities for him to engage with the present festivities and social interactions."</data>
      <data key="d5">chunk-843b5b2f944c7413d9ca876e2e2f151f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-90b95db5c53e4364a6bee36b7aa4d70f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-43c9bee23adfa77aa9dedd22401bba7d</data>
      <data key="d6">1</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;GHOST OF CHRISTMAS PRESENT&quot;" target="&quot;THE CITY&quot;">
      <data key="d3">8.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The Ghost of Christmas Present takes Scrooge to visit scenes within The City to show the joy and spirit of Christmas."</data>
      <data key="d5">chunk-843b5b2f944c7413d9ca876e2e2f151f</data>
      <data key="d6">1</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;GHOST OF CHRISTMAS YET TO COME&quot;" target="&quot;SCROOGE&quot;">
      <data key="d3">10.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"Scrooge is shown the future by the Ghost of Christmas Yet to Come, which deeply impacts his willingness to change."</data>
      <data key="d5">chunk-02baee20cc9463dbe08170a8e1043e32</data>
      <data key="d6">1</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;EBENEZER SCROOGE&quot;" target="&quot;JACOB MARLEY&quot;">
      <data key="d3">18.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"Jacob Marley was the business partner of Ebenezer Scrooge before Marley's death."&lt;SEP&gt;"Scrooge and Marley were business partners, and Marley's ghost now visits Scrooge to warn him about his way of life."</data>
      <data key="d5">chunk-359187e7571bda4b0b08b2e0b6581e52&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1aa50206d02ed89418f65f97c6441d1c</data>
      <data key="d6">1</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;EBENEZER SCROOGE&quot;" target="&quot;MARLEY'S GHOST&quot;">
      <data key="d3">19.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"Scrooge is directly confronted by Marley's Ghost, forcing him to acknowledge the supernatural and reevaluate his beliefs."&lt;SEP&gt;"Scrooge is haunted by Marley's Ghost, which deeply affects his mental state and his perception of time and reality."</data>
      <data key="d5">chunk-c7b10789a9cb0af6c553730b29bd9034&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1aa50206d02ed89418f65f97c6441d1c</data>
