    <edge source="&quot;MARLEY&quot;" target="&quot;SCROOGE&quot;">
      <data key="d3">31.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"Marley is part of Scrooge's past, referenced to show the shared experiences and possible influence on Scrooge's character."&lt;SEP&gt;"Scrooge and Marley had a past association, and even after Marley's death, his memory and ghostly presence continue to haunt Scrooge."&lt;SEP&gt;"Scrooge and Marley were business partners, and Marley's ghostly appearance symbolizes a connection beyond death, serving as a forewarning to Scrooge."&lt;SEP&gt;"Scrooge and Marley were long-time business partners, with their firm known as Scrooge and Marley. Their partnership is significant as Scrooge continues to use the business name even after Marley's death."</data>
      <data key="d5">chunk-843b5b2f944c7413d9ca876e2e2f151f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-89777b838d5447c7bd1ec11282c4ee89&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d9aac3484185ac66045df92214d245d5</data>
