      <data key="d6">1</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;CHRISTMAS EVE&quot;" target="&quot;SCROOGE&quot;">
      <data key="d3">7.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"Scrooge's disdain for the spirit of Christmas is highlighted during Christmas Eve, contrasting with the festive joy of others."</data>
      <data key="d5">chunk-d9aac3484185ac66045df92214d245d5</data>
      <data key="d6">1</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;SCROOGE'S COUNTING-HOUSE&quot;" target="&quot;SCROOGE&quot;">
      <data key="d3">9.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"Scrooge owns and operates his counting-house, maintaining control over its frugal and cold environment."</data>
      <data key="d5">chunk-74e2466de2f67fd710ef2f20c0a8d9e0</data>
      <data key="d6">1</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;NEPHEW&quot;" target="&quot;SCROOGE&quot;">
      <data key="d3">8.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"Scrooge and his nephew have a familial relationship characterized by differing views on Christmas, with the nephew advocating for festive cheer and Scrooge rejecting it."</data>
      <data key="d5">chunk-5dac41b3f9eeaf794f0147400b1718cd</data>
      <data key="d6">1</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;CLERK&quot;" target="&quot;SCROOGE&quot;">
      <data key="d3">6.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"Scrooge threatens the clerk over his response to Christmas enthusiasm, demonstrating a power dynamic where Scrooge holds authority."</data>
      <data key="d5">chunk-5dac41b3f9eeaf794f0147400b1718cd</data>
      <data key="d6">1</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;MR. MARLEY&quot;" target="&quot;SCROOGE&quot;">
      <data key="d3">7.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"Scrooge and Mr. Marley were business partners, with Marley having passed away seven years ago, leaving Scrooge to continue their business."</data>
      <data key="d5">chunk-5dac41b3f9eeaf794f0147400b1718cd</data>
      <data key="d6">1</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;PORTLY GENTLEMEN&quot;" target="&quot;SCROOGE&quot;">
      <data key="d3">5.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The portly gentlemen approach Scrooge for charitable donations during Christmas, highlighting a societal expectation of generosity which Scrooge dismisses."</data>
      <data key="d5">chunk-5dac41b3f9eeaf794f0147400b1718cd</data>
      <data key="d6">1</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;SCROOGE AND MARLEY'S&quot;" target="&quot;SCROOGE&quot;">
      <data key="d3">9.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"Scrooge is the surviving partner of the firm Scrooge and Marley's, indicating his ongoing control and management of the business."</data>
      <data key="d5">chunk-5dac41b3f9eeaf794f0147400b1718cd</data>
      <data key="d6">1</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;CHRISTMAS&quot;" target="&quot;SCROOGE&quot;">
      <data key="d3">25.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"Christmas acts as a catalyst for Scrooge's memories and reflections guided by the Ghost."&lt;SEP&gt;"Christmas serves as a time of reflection and emotional struggle for Scrooge within the narrative."&lt;SEP&gt;"The event of Christmas challenges Scrooge’s initial beliefs and behaviors, pushing him towards personal transformation."</data>
      <data key="d5">chunk-843b5b2f944c7413d9ca876e2e2f151f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-da2472b4ef2a535b62908f14d0fb0ca9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c6c248858d1b13ab7ee9ca13c1aeed6b</data>
      <data key="d6">1</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;CHRISTMAS&quot;" target="&quot;BLIND MAN'S BUFF&quot;">
      <data key="d3">8.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"Blind Man's Buff is one of the games played during the Christmas festivities, adding to the joyful and lively atmosphere."</data>
      <data key="d5">chunk-43c9bee23adfa77aa9dedd22401bba7d</data>
      <data key="d6">1</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;CHRISTMAS&quot;" target="&quot;FORFEITS&quot;">
      <data key="d3">8.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"Forfeits is another game played as part of the Christmas celebrations, contributing to the spirit of fun and community engagement."</data>
      <data key="d5">chunk-43c9bee23adfa77aa9dedd22401bba7d</data>
      <data key="d6">1</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;THE GENTLEMAN&quot;" target="&quot;SCROOGE&quot;">
      <data key="d3">8.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"Scrooge and The Gentleman have a direct interaction where Scrooge refuses to contribute to the charity efforts led by the Gentlement during Christmas."</data>
      <data key="d5">chunk-90d5764e301321c087f5a8f78b73a145</data>
      <data key="d6">1</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;UNION WORKHOUSES&quot;" target="&quot;SCROOGE&quot;">
      <data key="d3">6.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"Scrooge refers to Union Workhouses as a place for the poor, indicating his view that they provide necessary support."</data>
      <data key="d5">chunk-90d5764e301321c087f5a8f78b73a145</data>
      <data key="d6">1</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;THE TREADMILL AND THE POOR LAW&quot;" target="&quot;SCROOGE&quot;">
      <data key="d3">7.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"Scrooge believes that The Treadmill and The Poor Law are effective in dealing with poverty, indicating his indifference to the plight of the poor."</data>
      <data key="d5">chunk-90d5764e301321c087f5a8f78b73a145</data>
      <data key="d6">1</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;MANSION HOUSE&quot;" target="&quot;THE LORD MAYOR&quot;">
      <data key="d3">9.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The Lord Mayor presides over events at the Mansion House, particularly during Christmas, showcasing tradition and authority."</data>
      <data key="d5">chunk-90d5764e301321c087f5a8f78b73a145</data>
      <data key="d6">1</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;CAMDEN TOWN&quot;" target="&quot;SCROOGE&quot;">
      <data key="d3">6.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"Scrooge comments on the need for a cab to transport the turkey to Camden Town, showing attention to logistics and care for the gift's delivery."</data>
      <data key="d5">chunk-8f738cb25d60a7dab782162d9d0a25ed</data>
      <data key="d6">1</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;CITY OF LONDON&quot;" target="&quot;THE FOG AND FROST&quot;">
      <data key="d3">6.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The Fog and Frost envelop the City of London, creating a dreary and cold atmosphere around Scrooge."</data>
      <data key="d5">chunk-d9aac3484185ac66045df92214d245d5</data>
      <data key="d6">1</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;THE COUNTING-HOUSE&quot;" target="&quot;SCROOGE&quot;">
      <data key="d3">8.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The Counting-house is Scrooge's workplace, where he demonstrates his miserly nature and interacts with Bob Cratchit."</data>
      <data key="d5">chunk-d9aac3484185ac66045df92214d245d5</data>
      <data key="d6">1</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;THE KNOCKER&quot;" target="&quot;SCROOGE&quot;">
      <data key="d3">8.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The sight of Marley's face in the knocker terrifies Scrooge, marking the beginning of his supernatural experiences."</data>
      <data key="d5">chunk-d9aac3484185ac66045df92214d245d5</data>
      <data key="d6">1</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;MARLEY'S GHOST&quot;" target="&quot;SCROOGE&quot;">
      <data key="d3">17.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"Marley's Ghost appears to deliver a dire warning to Scrooge about the necessity of changing his ways."&lt;SEP&gt;"Scrooge encounters Marley's Ghost, which challenges his skepticism and forces him to confront supernatural realities."</data>
      <data key="d5">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cb661c37436355ccec2769b1d0350c5f</data>
      <data key="d6">1</data>
    </edge>
