      <data key="d5">chunk-1aa50206d02ed89418f65f97c6441d1c</data>
      <data key="d6">1</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;MARLEY'S GHOST&quot;" target="&quot;SPECTRE&quot;">
      <data key="d3">8.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The term Spectre represents the ghostly form of Marley's Ghost, emphasizing its eerie presence."</data>
      <data key="d5">chunk-1aa50206d02ed89418f65f97c6441d1c</data>
      <data key="d6">1</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;MARLEY'S GHOST&quot;" target="&quot;INFERNAL ATMOSPHERE&quot;">
      <data key="d3">8.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"Marley's Ghost is surrounded by an Infernal Atmosphere, adding to its supernatural and unsettling nature."</data>
      <data key="d5">chunk-1aa50206d02ed89418f65f97c6441d1c</data>
      <data key="d6">1</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;MARLEY'S GHOST&quot;" target="&quot;THE BANDAGE&quot;">
      <data key="d3">8.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The Bandage is part of Marley's Ghost's appearance, removed to reveal its spectral form more vividly."</data>
      <data key="d5">chunk-1aa50206d02ed89418f65f97c6441d1c</data>
      <data key="d6">1</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;MARLEY'S GHOST&quot;" target="&quot;THE THREE SPIRITS&quot;">
      <data key="d3">8.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"Marley's Ghost informs Scrooge that he will be visited by the Three Spirits as part of his chance for redemption."</data>
      <data key="d5">chunk-cb661c37436355ccec2769b1d0350c5f</data>
      <data key="d6">1</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;JACOB MARLEY&quot;" target="&quot;THE CHAIN&quot;">
      <data key="d3">9.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The Chain is worn by Marley's Ghost, representing the consequences of Jacob Marley's earthly actions and choices."</data>
      <data key="d5">chunk-1aa50206d02ed89418f65f97c6441d1c</data>
      <data key="d6">1</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;JACOB MARLEY&quot;" target="&quot;CHAINS&quot;">
      <data key="d3">9.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"Jacob Marley is burdened by the metaphorical chains he forged in life due to his actions and attitudes toward others."</data>
      <data key="d5">chunk-359187e7571bda4b0b08b2e0b6581e52</data>
      <data key="d6">1</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;JACOB MARLEY&quot;" target="&quot;CHRISTMAS EVES&quot;">
      <data key="d3">8.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"Jacob Marley refers to 'seven Christmas Eves' since his death, emphasizing the duration of his penance."</data>
      <data key="d5">chunk-359187e7571bda4b0b08b2e0b6581e52</data>
      <data key="d6">1</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;JACOB MARLEY&quot;" target="&quot;SCROOGE&quot;">
      <data key="d3">41.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"Jacob Marley as a ghost warns Scrooge about his fate and urges him to listen to the Three Spirits."&lt;SEP&gt;"Jacob Marley's influence is significant in Scrooge's reflection and transformation regarding Christmas and life changes."&lt;SEP&gt;"Jacob Marley's intervention is pivotal as he sends spirits to guide and reform Scrooge."&lt;SEP&gt;"Scrooge frequently references Jacob Marley, indicating Marley's influence on his change of heart and perspective."&lt;SEP&gt;"Scrooge remembers Jacob Marley's prediction about Spirits visiting him, which influences his reactions to these supernatural events."</data>
      <data key="d5">chunk-91572b3cd42786ba4cb2f180ca25cbf4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-da2472b4ef2a535b62908f14d0fb0ca9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-90b95db5c53e4364a6bee36b7aa4d70f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cb661c37436355ccec2769b1d0350c5f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-02baee20cc9463dbe08170a8e1043e32</data>
      <data key="d6">1</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;THE GHOST&quot;" target="&quot;WARD&quot;">
      <data key="d3">5.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The Ward is humorously referenced as a location that could charge the Ghost for being a public nuisance due to its cries and clanking chains."</data>
      <data key="d5">chunk-359187e7571bda4b0b08b2e0b6581e52</data>
      <data key="d6">1</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;THE GHOST&quot;" target="&quot;SCROOGE&quot;">
      <data key="d3">57.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"Scrooge engages in a conversation with The Ghost about Tiny Tim's future, indicating his growing concern and transformation."&lt;SEP&gt;"Scrooge is accompanied by The Ghost, who shows him various scenes to teach him the error of his ways."&lt;SEP&gt;"Scrooge is being guided by The Ghost through memories, prompting introspection and lessons about his previous actions."&lt;SEP&gt;"Scrooge is directly confronted by The Ghost, who is the spectral embodiment of his former partner Jacob Marley, warning him about his life choices."&lt;SEP&gt;"Scrooge is guided by The Ghost through different places and experiences to learn about Christmas spirit."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Ghost guides Scrooge through memories of his past, prompting personal reflection."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Ghost leads Scrooge through reflections of his past, acting as a guide to explore his emotions and memories."</data>
      <data key="d5">chunk-503f0bfa5453467c7c61d160a3540eca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cb661c37436355ccec2769b1d0350c5f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-91614df5cb74cbe5e109a338a82041e9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b2f98bc7abb0c67d4c86055c7fd72218&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c6c248858d1b13ab7ee9ca13c1aeed6b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e7637ff18c5ded77a68cce0a87883fad&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8590d9263cd2cd4fa583c432fc54e6c3</data>
      <data key="d6">1</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;THE GHOST&quot;" target="&quot;TWELFTH-NIGHT PARTY&quot;">
      <data key="d3">7.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The Ghost takes Scrooge to visit a Twelfth-Night party as part of his enlightening journey."</data>
      <data key="d5">chunk-e7637ff18c5ded77a68cce0a87883fad</data>
      <data key="d6">1</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;THE THREE SPIRITS&quot;" target="&quot;SCROOGE&quot;">
      <data key="d3">9.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"Scrooge is forewarned by Marley's Ghost that he will be visited by the Three Spirits, which are crucial for his chance at redemption."</data>
      <data key="d5">chunk-cb661c37436355ccec2769b1d0350c5f</data>
      <data key="d6">1</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;THE PHANTOMS&quot;" target="&quot;SCROOGE&quot;">
      <data key="d3">7.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"Scrooge observes the Phantoms outside his window, realizing the consequences of neglecting human connections and compassion in life."</data>
      <data key="d5">chunk-cb661c37436355ccec2769b1d0350c5f</data>
      <data key="d6">1</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;THE PHANTOMS&quot;" target="&quot;THE INFANTS&quot;">
      <data key="d3">7.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The Phantoms witness The Infants from spirits above without power to assist, symbolizing their eternal regret for neglecting compassion in their lives."</data>
      <data key="d5">chunk-cb661c37436355ccec2769b1d0350c5f</data>
      <data key="d6">1</data>
    </edge>
